sentences: He studied at Heidelberg University and the Stern conservatory in Berlin, but left Germany in 1933, going to Basle, where he received his doctorate.
In 1939 he moved to the United States where he remained, becoming a U.S. citizen.
He taught at the University of California, Berkeley from 1941 until his premature death from multiple myeloma.

sentences: Manfred Fritz Bukofzer (March 27, 1910 – December 7, 1955) was a German-American musicologist and humanist.
In addition to Baroque music, he was a specialist in English music and music theory of the 14th through 16th centuries.

His book Music in the Baroque Era is still one of the standard reference works on the topic, though some modern historians assert that it has a Germanic bias, for instance in minimizing the importance of opera (Italian by origin) during the development of musical style in the 17th century.
